Press.</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 2011. &ldquo;A neo-Aristotelian substance
ontology: neither relational nor constituent&rdquo;, in
<em>Contemporary Aristotelian Metaphysics</em>, Tuomas Tahko (ed.),
Cambridge: Cambridge University Press.</li>

<li>Mackie, P., 2000. Review of Hoffman and Rosenkranz (1994),
<em>Mind</em>, 109: 149&ndash;152.</li>

<li>Marmodoro, A., 2013. &ldquo;Aristotle&rsquo;s hylomorphism without
reconditioning&rdquo;, <em>Philosophical Inquiry</em>, 37:
5&ndash;22.</li>

<li>Martin, C. B., 1980. &ldquo;Substance Substantiated&rdquo;,
<em>Australasian Journal of Philosophy</em>, 58(1): 3&ndash;10.</li>

<li>McEvilley, T., 2002. <em>The Shape of Ancient Thought: Comparative
