<li>Nagel, E., 1961. <em>The Structure of Science</em>, London:
Routledge.</li>

<li>Nagel, T., 2012. <em>Mind and Cosmos</em>, Oxford and New York:
Oxford University Press.</li>

<li>Nussbaum, M. (tr. and ed.), 1978. <em>Aristotle: De Motu
Animalium</em>, Princeton: Princeton University Press.</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 1984. &ldquo;Aristotelian dualism: reply to
Howard Robinson&rdquo;, <em>Oxford Studies in Ancient Philosophy</em>,
2: 197&ndash;207.</li>

<li>O&rsquo;Conaill, D., 2022. <em>Substance</em>, Cambridge:
Cambridge University Press. </li>

<li>Owens, J., 1951. <em>The Doctrine of Being in the Aristotelian
Metaphysics</em>, Toronto: Pontifical Institute.</li>

<li>Paul, L., 2002. &ldquo;Logical parts&rdquo;, <em>No&ucirc;s</em>,
36: 578&ndash;96.</li>

<li>Pini, G., 2008. &ldquo;Reading Aristotle&rsquo;s Categories as an
Introduction to Logic: Later Medieval Discussions about its Place in
the Aristotelian Corpus&rdquo;, in <em>Medieval Commentaries on
Aristotle&rsquo;s Categories</em>, L. Newton (ed.), Leiden: Brill,
148&ndash;51.</li>

<li>Plato, <em>Sophist</em>. N. White (trans. and ed.).  Indianapolis,
IN: Hackett, 1993.</li>

<li>Putnam, H., 1975. &ldquo;The meaning of
&lsquo;meaning&rsquo;&rdquo;, in his <em>Mind, Language and
Reality</em>, Cambridge: Cambridge University Press,
215&ndash;71.</li>

<li>Rea, M., 2011. &ldquo;Hylomorphism reconditioned&rdquo;,
<em>Philosophical Perspectives</em>, 25: 341&ndash;58.</li>

<li>Rea, M. (ed.), 1997. <em>Material Constitution</em>, Lanham, MD:
Rowman and Littlefield.</li>

<li>Robinson, H., 1983. &ldquo;Aristotelian dualism&rdquo;, <em>Oxford
Studies in Ancient Philosophy</em>, 1: 124&ndash;44.</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 2014. &ldquo;Naturalism and the
unavoidability of the Cartesian perspective&rdquo;, in A. Lavazza and
H. Robinson (eds.), <em>Contemporary Dualism</em>, London,
Routledge.</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 2016. <em>From the Knowledge Argument to
