Oxford University Press, 347&ndash;83.</li>

<li>Schechtman, A., 2016. &ldquo;Substance and Independence in
Descartes&rdquo;, <em>Philosophical Review</em>, 125: 155&ndash;204.
</li>

<li>Schillebeeckx, E., 1968. <em>The Eucharist</em>, New York, Burns
and Oates.</li>

<li>Schneider, B., 2006. &ldquo;A Certain Kind of Trinity: Dependence,
Substance, Explanation&rdquo;, <em>Philosophical Studies</em>, 129:
393&ndash;419. </li>

<li>Sider, T., 2001. <em>Four Dimensionalism</em>, Oxford, Oxford
University Press.</li>

<li>Simons, P. 1994. &ldquo;Particulars in particular clothing&rdquo;,
<em>Philosophy and Phenomenological Research</em>, 54:
553&ndash;575.</li>

<li>Simpson, S., 2021. &ldquo;From Quantum Physics to Classical
Metaphysics&rdquo;, in <em>Neo-Aristotelian Metaphysics and the
Theology of Nature</em>, W. Simpson, R. Koons, &amp; J. Orr (eds.),
London: Routledge, 21&ndash;65.</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 2023. Hylomorphism, Cambridge: Cambridge
University Press. </li>

<li>Solmsen, F., 1944. &ldquo;Boethius and the History of the
Organon&rdquo;, <em>American Journal of Philology</em>, 65:
69&ndash;74.</li>

<li>Spinoza, B., <em>Collected Works</em>, E. Curley (ed.),
Princeton: Princeton University Press, 1985.</li>

<li>Strawson, P. F., 1959. <em>Individuals</em>, London: Methuen.</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 1966. <em>The Bounds of Sense</em>, London:
Methuen.</li>

<li>Unger, P., 1975. <em>Ignorance: A Case for Scepticism</em>,
Oxford: Oxford University Press.</li>

<li>van Inwagen, P., 1990. <em>Material Beings</em>, Ithaca and
London: Cornell University Press.</li>

<li>Weir, R. S., 2021. &ldquo;Bring Back Substances!&rdquo;, <em>The
Review of Metaphysics</em>, 75(2): 265&ndash;308.</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 2023a. <em>The Mind-Body Problem and
Metaphysics: An Argument from Consciousness to Mental Substance</em>,
London: Routledge. </li>

<li>Wiggins, D., 1967. <em>Identity and Spatio-Temporal
Continuity</em>, Oxford: Blackwell.</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 1980. <em>Sameness and Substance</em>,
Oxford: Blackwell.</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 1997. &ldquo;Sortal concepts: a reply to
Xu&rdquo;, <em>Mind and Language</em>, 12: 413&ndash;21.</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 1998. &ldquo;Substance&rdquo;, in
<em>Philosophy 1: a Guide Through the Subject</em>, A. C. Grayling
(ed.), Oxford: Oxford University Press, 214&ndash;49.</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 2001. <em>Sameness and Substance
Renewed</em>, Cambridge: Cambridge University Press.</li>

<li>Woods, M., 1991. &ldquo;Universals and particular forms in
Aristotle&rsquo;s <em>Metaphysics</em>&rdquo;, in H. Blumenthal and H.
Robinson (eds.), <em>Aristotle and the Later Tradition</em>
(Oxford Studies in Ancient Philosophy: Supplementary Volume 1991),
Oxford: Oxford University Press, 41&ndash;56.</li>

<li>Woolhouse, R., 1982. &ldquo;The nature of an individual
substance&rdquo;, in <em>Leibniz: Critical and Interpretive
